INSERT INTO Paragraphs (ParagraphID, TopicID, Content) VALUES (1, 1, 'Introduction A complex number system is an extension of the real number system. Complex numbers are necessary to solve equations such as The symbol is introduced to stand for, so the previous equation has the two solutions. More generally, complex numbers are needed to solve for the two roots of a quadratic equation which, according to the quadratic formula, has the two solutions: Whenever the discriminant is negative, the solution must be expressed as a complex number. For example, the roots of are, because ');
