INSERT INTO Paragraphs (ParagraphID, TopicID, Content) VALUES (3, 2, 'Rectangular Form In rectangular form, all of the following notations define the same complex number. The ordered pair can be interpreted as a point in the two-dimensional plane. A complex number can also be drawn as a vector whose tail is at the origin and whose head is at the point, in which case is the horizontal coordinate of the vector and the vertical coordinate (see Fig.~※).  Complex number represented as a vector from the origin to. Figure~※ shows some numerical examples.  Complex numbers plotted as vectors in the two-dimensional “complex plane.” Each is represented by a vector from the origin to the point with coordinates in the complex plane. The complex number is represented by the point, which lies in the first quadrant of the two-dimensional plane; likewise, lies in the fourth quadrant at the location. Since the complex number notation represents the point in the two-dimensional plane, the number represents, which is drawn as a vertical vector from the origin up to, as in Fig.~※. Thus multiplying a real number, such as, by changes it from pointing along the horizontal axis to pointing vertically, i.e.,. Rectangular form is also referred to as Cartesian form. The horizontal coordinate is called the real part, and the vertical coordinate the imaginary part. The operators and are provided to extract the real and imaginary parts of :');
