INSERT INTO Paragraphs (ParagraphID, TopicID, Content) VALUES (12, 5, ' The MATLAB GUI zdrill for practicing complex number operations. Geometric View of Addition For complex addition,, both and are viewed as vectors with their tails at the origin. The sum is the result of vector addition, and is constructed as follows (see Fig.~※):  Draw a copy of with its tail at the head of. Call this displaced vector. Draw the vector from the origin to the head of. This vector is the sum. Graphical construction of complex number addition. This method of addition can be generalized to many vectors. Figure~※ shows the result of adding the four complex numbers where the answer happens to be zero.');
