INSERT INTO Paragraphs (ParagraphID, TopicID, Content) VALUES (28, 12, 'MATLAB Built-in Functions Many MATLAB functions operate on arrays just as easily as they operate on scalars. For example, if x is an array, then cos(x) returns an array of the same size as x containing the cosine of each element of x. Notice that no loop is needed, even though cos(x) does apply the cosine function to every array element. Most transcendental functions follow this pointwise rule. In some cases, it is crucial to make this distinction, such as the matrix exponential (expm) versus the pointwise exponential (exp): ');
