INSERT INTO Paragraphs (ParagraphID, TopicID, Content) VALUES (39, 15, ' y = x; jkl = find(y > Limit); y( jkl ) = Limit; jkl = find(y < -Limit); y( jkl ) = -Limit; Seek to Vectorize The dictum to “avoid for loops” is not always easy to obey, because it means the algorithm must be cast in a vector form. If matrix-vector notation is incorporated into MATLAB programs, the resulting code will run much faster. Even loops with logical tests can be vectorized if masks are created for all possible conditions. Thus, a reasonable goal is the following:');
