INSERT INTO Paragraphs (ParagraphID, TopicID, Content) VALUES (145, 64, 'Relation to Impulse Response and Difference Equation can be calculated directly from the filter coefficients. If is compared to, we see that, given the difference equation, it is simple to write down an expression for by noting that each term in corresponds to a term or in, and vice versa. Likewise, can be determined directly from the impulse response since the impulse response of the FIR system consists of the sequence of filter coefficients; i.e., for. To emphasize this point, we can write the correspondence   The process of going from the difference equation or impulse response to the frequency response is straightforward for the FIR filter. It is also simple to go from the frequency response to the difference equation or to the impulse response if we express in terms of powers of. These points are illustrated by the following examples. EXAMPLE:  }] Consider the FIR filter defined by the impulse response By inspection, the sequence of filter coefficients is, so the difference equation corresponding to this impulse response is and the frequency response of this system is  EXAMPLE:  Difference Equation from Suppose that the frequency response is given by the equation Since, we can write which corresponds to the following FIR difference equation: The impulse response, likewise, is easy to determine directly from, when expressed in terms of powers of. Use the inverse Euler formula for sines to find the impulse response and difference equation for.');
