INSERT INTO Paragraphs (ParagraphID, TopicID, Content) VALUES (184, 79, 'Inherent Periodicity of in the DFT In this section we will study more properties of the DFT/IDFT. In the previous section, we examined properties of the DFT which are are tied to its interpretation as a frequency sampled version of the DTFT, and the fact that is periodic. This periodicity affects the placement of negative frequency components in, and also symmetries. In this section, we want to show that the IDFT summation requires that the signal must be periodic with period. This property might be surprising because the DFT has been defined for a finite-length -point sequence, and the DFT yields DFT coefficients. However, some transform properties implicitly involve operations that evaluate the indices or outside of, so periodicity is needed to explain properties such as the delay property and convolution.');
