INSERT INTO Paragraphs (ParagraphID, TopicID, Content) VALUES (240, 101, 'System Function of an IIR Filter We saw in Chapter ※ for the FIR case that the system function is the -transform of the impulse response of the system, and that the system function and the frequency response are intimately related. Furthermore, the following result was shown:   The same is true for the IIR case. The system function for an FIR filter is always a polynomial; however, when the difference equation has feedback, it turns out that the system function is the ratio of two polynomials. Ratios of polynomials are called rational functions. In this section we will determine the system function for the example of a first-order IIR system, and show how the system function, impulse response, and difference equation are related.');
