INSERT INTO Paragraphs (ParagraphID, TopicID, Content) VALUES (256, 107, 'Second-Order Filters We now turn our attention to filters with two feedback coefficients, and. The general difference equation becomes the second-order difference equation As before, we can characterize the second-order filter in each of the three domains: time domain, frequency domain, and -domain. We start with the -transform domain because by now we have demonstrated that the poles and zeros of the system function give a great deal of insight into most aspects of both the time and frequency responses.');
